The main reason for your issue is that you&#39;re trying to compare between `ArrayList` and `UnmodifiableList` (or `UnmodifiableRandomAccessList`), and those are obviously not the same objects...

Now let&#39;s look at the details.

If you check `Arrays.of(...)` implementation you would find the following:

```java
    public static &lt;T&gt; List&lt;T&gt; asList(T... a) {
        return new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(a);
    }
```

while if you look at `Collections.unmodifiableList(...)` you would find:

```java
    public static &lt;T&gt; List&lt;T&gt; unmodifiableList(List&lt;? extends T&gt; list) {
        if (list.getClass() == UnmodifiableList.class || list.getClass() == UnmodifiableRandomAccessList.class) {
           return (List&lt;T&gt;) list;
        }

        return (list instanceof RandomAccess ?
                new UnmodifiableRandomAccessList&lt;&gt;(list) :
                new UnmodifiableList&lt;&gt;(list));
    }
```

As you can see, the 2 methods return different types of objects, and therefore the `equals()` method returns `false`.

