[What does `entrySet` returns?][1]

    public Set&lt;Map.Entry&lt;K,V&gt;&gt; entrySet()
&gt;Returns a Set view of the mappings contained in this map. The set is backed by the map, so changes to the map are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. 

If you want iterate over the `myWordDict` hash map then just  

    for(Map.Entry&lt;String, Set&lt;Integer&gt;&gt; entry : myWordDict.entrySet())
    {
       Set&lt;Integer&gt; newVariable = entry.getValue();
    }

**Related links**  

 - [Map.Entry#getValue()][2]


  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/HashMap.html#entrySet%28%29
  [2]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Map.Entry.html#getValue%28%29

